              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "*By authors*.Absolute normalization of differential",
                " cross section depends mainly (apart from temperature",
                " correction uncertainty) on the accuracy of Arndt's",
                " phase-shift prediction for pp scattering and the",
                " final absolute normalization to be good to within 2.5%",
                " the absolute normalization of analyzing power hinges",
                " on the normalization of polarization which in turn",
                " depends on the normalization of the measured analyzing",
                " power data in p-carbon scattering the overall absolute",
                " uncertainty to be +-0.02."
